Sixteen normal healthy adult volunteers agreed to take part in an investigation to define the normal concentration of urine fibrin-degradation products (F.D.P.) for our laboratory. 20 ml of urine was collected daily in the early morning for a month, dialysed against tap-water, concentrated in polyethylene glycol at 4&deg;C overnight, and stored at -18&deg;C until assay. 


